<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Global Markets Operations/Middle Office Group (GMO&amp;MO) provides controlled and efficient pre and post-trade processes in support of our revenue generating businesses. Core functions include post confirmation, settlement and client services processes as well as assurance over data and processes used to record risk, P/L, balance sheet and financial results. The organization is aligned to products and business management:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Global Middle Office delivers control functions responsible for providing assurance over data and processes used to record risk, P/L, balance sheet and financial results in support of Global Markets, Corporate Treasury and Corporate Investments businesses</li>
	<li>Global Markets Fixed Income Operations and Client Services delivers trading, sales and syndicate support, funding, clearance, settlement, and other core operational services to the Global Markets businesses for fixed income and traded loan products, as well as the Corporate Treasury and Investment Portfolio businesses across all products. Also provides client and product reference data services across all products and regions globally</li>
	<li>Global Equity Operations delivers trading, sales and syndicate support for the Equity business in the Americas. Provides operational support for across products for Global Markets businesses in Latin America and Canada</li>
	<li>Global Markets Projects and Change Management provides quality oversight as it relates to managing operational risk, overall associate satisfaction and key strategic initiatives as well as providing efficient and effective delivery of prioritized change management initiatives</li>
	<li>Global Derivatives, Foreign Exchange, Futures and Commodities Operations provides confirmation, settlement, and customer service processes for the Global Interest Rate Derivative, Credit Derivative, Equity Derivative, Foreign Exchange, Commodity, and Futures businesses</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Programme Overview:</h2>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>The primary goal of the GMOMO Programme will be to develop exceptional analysts</li>
	<li>The programme will be 3 years, with the option to rotate through middle office and operations</li>
	<li>During the first year of the programme, participants will engage in a number of activities that will develop skills in networking, relationship building, learn &#64; lunch,  and complete a comprehensive learning curriculum</li>
	<li>Subject to satisfactory performance, participants will be offered opportunity to study for Investment Administration Qualification (IAQ), Chartered Institute of Management Accountants (CIMA) or Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) in their 2<sup>nd</sup> & 3<sup>rd</sup> years. In addition Six Sigma training will be offered to attain the Green Belt accreditation</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Candidates in their final year of study, expecting to graduate in 2010 and those who graduated in 2009 are eligible to apply. Candidates must demonstrate a combination of academic aptitude, quantitative skills, strategic and creative thinking and written and oral communications skills. In addition you must have obtained or are realistically expecting to obtain a minimum 2:1 degree or equivalent. Analysts will be required to prioritise, multi-task and work effectively both individually and as part of a team.
</p>
<p class="bac">
Some common driving characteristics we look for:
</p>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>Attention to detail</li>
	<li>Exceptional academic achievement</li>
	<li>Initiative; team focus</li>
	<li>Leadership</li>
	<li>Strategic and creative thinking capabilities</li>
	<li>Strong work ethic</li>
	<li>Strong communication skills</li>
	<li>Dedication to a career in middle office or global operations</li>
	<li>A penchant for identifying and resolving problems proactively</li>
	<li>Technology proficiency</li>
</ul>

